1) node_modules: This directory contains the dependencies and packages installed via npm or Yarn.

2) public: This directory contains the static assets and the HTML file that serves as the entry point for the application. 
           The index.html file is where the React application is mounted.

3) src: This is the main source code directory where most of your application code resides.
   a) assets: This directory is used to store static assets such as images, fonts, or other media files.
   b) components: React components that are used throughout the application. 
   c) pages: React components that represent individual pages or views of the application. Each page may consist of multiple components.
   d) App.js: The main component that acts as the root component for the entire application.
   e) index.js: The entry point for the React application. It typically renders the App component into the root HTML element defined in public/index.html.

4) package.json: Configuration file that contains metadata about the project and lists dependencies, scripts, and other settings.
